        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12654",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I would like to change the MONTH constants like this:\n\nMONTH -> 2 digits monthnumber\nMONTH_SHORT -> 1 or 2 digits monthnumber\n\nMONTHNAME -> full locale aware monthname\nMONTHNAME_SHORT -> 2-4 letter abbreviated monthname\nMONTHNAME_NARROW -> 1 letter abbreviated monthname\n\nThis would be more accurate and reflect the needs more like the DAY and WEEKDAY constants.\n\nYour opinion ?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-09T13:00:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-09T13:00:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12658",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If we use MONTH_NAME, MONTH_NAME_SHORT, and MONTH_NAME_NARROW, then I think your proposed changes are intuitive.\n\nWe should be careful to keep the docu sysnchronized with any changes to these constants.\n\nHowever, this change might result in another inconsistency regarding weekday names.  In PHP's date() documentation, weekday names are called \"a full textual representation of the day of the week\".  Given the uniquely international flavor of the Zend Framework and community, is \"weekday\" or \"day_name\" better for non-native English speakers?\n\nPersonally, I really like your proposed changes above, because \"month_name*\" is very clear to me, and should be easy to understand by non-native English speakers.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-09T14:35:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-09T14:35:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12672",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Better is weekday... because day always is related to day within month.\nAnd most other languages have weekday instead of dayname.\n\nWhich name would the day '12' have ? \n\nYou could say DAY_OF_WEEK or WEEKDAY... WEEKDAY is in my eyes better reflecting the coupling to WEEK instead of day.\n\nI would like to have WEEKDAY (and I am non-native english).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-10T07:19:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-10T07:19:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12673",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed with SVN 3337.\n\nMonth names were changed like this:\n\nMONTH_SHORT  -> MONTH\nMONTH_DIGIT  -> MONTH_SHORT\nMONTH        -> MONTH_NAME\nMONTH_NAME   -> MONTH_NAME_SHORT\nMONTH_NARROW -> MONTH_NAME_NARROW\n\nDocu must be reworked for reflecting this changes",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-10T07:51:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-10T07:51:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12697",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "{quote}And most other languages have weekday instead of dayname.{quote}\n\nOk.  I only know English and some Vietnamese.  This is good to know.\n\nThe name of day 12 depends on the year and month, but would be either Sunday, Monday, Tuesday, etc., but in the language selected by locale.  I vote to follow your recommendation for keeping WEEKDAY, and now wonder about PHP's documentation for date(), where they use \"day of week\".  Perhaps they should alter their docs ;)\n\nUpdating docu ....",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-12T17:40:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-12T17:40:16.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
